    Contributing

    We welcome all contributions to this project! If you notice a bug, or have a feature request, please open up an issue here.

    The group members will contribute by working in a branhch-feature approach, meaning each new feature or fix will be implemented and tested in its own branch and submitted for peer review by a Pull Request before being incorporated into the main working branch.

    If you’d like to contribute a feature or bug fix, and you are not a group member, we encourage you to fork our repository and submit your fix or new feature using a Pull Request. We will review pull requests within 7 days. All contributors must abide by our code of conduct.

    (Note: The text above is based off a template taken from the UBC DSCI310 website)
